	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This Japanese game was from Konami and used  &quot;Konamiâ€™s Response Sound System&quot;<br />The game features a lot of vocals handled outside of the SPC, the cart connector's L/R analog audio channels..<br />The cart featured an SA-1 chip and I believe the SA-1 handled the digital voice and fed it to an external DAC on the cart which was fed to the Left/Right analog audio channels on the cart connector. Does that sound right?<br /><br />gameplay footage: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LDEl1-tuzc4">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LDEl1-tuzc4</a><!-- m -->

		

